侧重有洞察、领悟事物细微差别以及微妙关系的能力。
普通用词，含义广泛，语气最强，指优美和谐，是一种几乎接近完美的美。指人时通常形容女人或小孩，很少用于描写男子。
普通用词，描写人时，主要指女人和小孩的相貌，语气不如beautiful强。

普通用词，语气比beautiful弱，多用于描写妇女、儿童以及小巧玲珑，精美可爱之物。
正式用词，多用于文学中，形容女子和儿童，侧重外表的美。

list.abstract: fine，英文单词，可作形容词、动词、名词和副词，在句中作表语、状语等，翻译为很好的，不错。

法音，太阳般闪耀的女孩。
虽然，没有太多人喜欢这个淳朴的孩子。
但是，她在我的心里，永恒。。。

yingyinNormal.en: Riley? Yeah? You're fired. Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱丽？干啥？你被解雇了。好的。

yingyinNormal.en: Joy. Joy, he's really doing fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，乔伊，他现在真的挺好的。

yingyinNormal.en: Will you get us better gifts? Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你会送我们更好的礼物吗？好啦。

yingyinNormal.en: So, how was your day at school? Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天在学校过得怎么样？挺好的。

yingyinNormal.en: You must have your boarding pass. Ok. Fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小姐，您必须要有登机牌。好的好的。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. That's fine. Great. Okay, good for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没关系好的。太棒了，很好。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, Everybody's okay. We're fine. We're okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，我们都没事。我们都挺好的。

yingyinNormal.en: You guys are gonna be fine. We all will be fine. We have to be fine. Okay? Smackle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们会过得很好的。我们都会很好的。我们一定要很好。好吗？史麦科。

yingyinNormal.en: No, it's not going to be fine. Change is never fine. They say it is, but it's not.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不可能会好了，改变总是不好的，人们说改变是好事，事实才不是。

yingyinNormal.en: How did it go? Fine. I think. I didn't mess my bit up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 音乐会怎么样？我觉得挺好的，起码我没犯错。

yingyinNormal.en: How's this look? It's fine. Where'd you get that picture of her?
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么样？挺好的，你哪弄来的她的照片？

yingyinNormal.en: It's okay. I'm gonna be fine. Come here, I'll make you a drink. Okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没事。过来，我给你弄点喝的。 好的

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Kalinda, it's Will. How are things there? Uh, yeah, they're fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好。凯琳达，我是威尔，你那情况如何？挺好的。

yingyinNormal.en: We have many fine women. Ninat is the best singer. But I don't want Ninat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们这有很多好姑娘，妮奈是最好的歌手。我不想要妮奈。

yingyinNormal.en: That's fine. But please save some food for the picnic. Yes, Madam Gazelle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那请留些食物等会儿野餐再吃。好的，羚羊夫人。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm so sorry. Is he okay? Yeah, he's gonna be fine, but he's heavily sedated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我很抱歉。他还好吧？是的，他们说他会好的。但他还是得服药静养。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. Then I'll take you to the Hare and the Hatter, but that's the end of it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，那我把你带到三月兔和疯帽子那里去，我能做的只有这样了。

yingyinNormal.en: Honey, a couple of short stacks of pancakes like us can do just fine. And a superklutz!
yingyinNormal.zh: 亲爱的，像我们这样的矮煎饼堆也可以活得好好的。超级大笨瓜也是！

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. That's fine. But I think that you might be really interested in our second model.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，这很好，并且我认为我们的第二款产品，会让你非常感兴趣的

yingyinNormal.en: Even when you were a kid and you were chubby and you had no friends, you were just fine.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就连你小时候，胖嘟嘟的，一个朋友也没有的时候，你还是活得好好的。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Companies that contributed more to political campaigns did not receive lower <highlight>fines</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对政治活动作出更多贡献的公司并没有被处以更少的罚金。

examination_example.sentence: Using a fashion model that does not meet a government-defined index could result in a $85, 000 <highlight>fine</highlight> and six months in prison.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 使用不符合政府规定指数的时装模特可能会导致8.5万美元的罚款和六个月的监禁。

examination_example.sentence: But if you go on automatic pilot, you're <highlight>fine</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: The rich own the robots, so they will be <highlight>fine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 富人拥有机器人，所以他们不会受影响。

examination_example.sentence: In the past couple of weeks a quarrel has illustrated the value to advertisers of such <highlight>fine</highlight>-grained information.

word_usage.usage:
表示“健康、好”
well指健康、身体好，尤用以谈自己的健康、询问别人的健康或评价身体情况。
fine（不用于否定句）指身体很好、健康，尤用于回应别人的询问，表示自己身体很健康。与well不一样，fine通常不用于询问别人的身体状况或者谈论身体情况。
All right和OK指感觉身体还好、没有生病、没有受伤，口语中使用。

word_usage.usage: 表示“美好的, 优秀的”时，fine有比较级finer和最高级finest。
表“健康的, 身体很好的”时，fine没有比较级和最高级。

fine表“天气晴朗的”时，主语多用it。
示例：It was another fine winter day. 
又是一个晴朗的冬日。
fine表“罚金”时，为可数名词，注意单复数。

fine作动词，表“处...以罚金”时，多以被动形式出现。
示例：She was fined for speeding.
她因超速而被罚款。

examination_example.sentence: We all want to hope things will turn out <highlight>fine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们都希望事情会好转。

examination_example.sentence: Whatever it is, the result is a <highlight>fine</highlight> and vivid description of the purest of Central Asian traditions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不管是什么，其结果都是对中亚最纯粹的传统的美好而生动的描述。

examination_example.sentence: If the weather is <highlight>fine</highlight>, we can have a barbecue in the garden.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果天气好的话，我们可以在花园里烧烤。

examination_example.sentence: That's totally <highlight>fine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那完全没问题。

examination_example.sentence: The pronunciation is <highlight>fine</highlight> with me, and its vocabulary is similar to English.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 发音对我来说很容易接受，它的词汇和英语很相似。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Fine</highlight> with me.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我没问题。

examination_example.sentence: I examined the chick (雏鸟) and it seemed <highlight>fine</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence: Oh, hi, Frank, just <highlight>fine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 嗨，弗兰克，我很好。

examination_example.sentence: I didn't come from a family with wealth or position, but I did manage to get a master's degree in <highlight>fine</highlight> arts.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我的家庭并不富裕，地位也不高，但我确实取得了美术硕士学位。

examination_example.sentence: I didn't tell you this during the season, but you did <highlight>fine</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 赛季的时候我没告诉你，但你做得很好。

examination_example.sentence: They were more likely to break the speed limit and be at risk of getting <highlight>fined</highlight>.

examination_example.sentence_trans: 消防队员把女孩带到外面，医生检查后发现她没事。

examination_example.sentence: As a young man, Jack was an excellent artist with a wife and two <highlight>fine</highlight> sons.

examination_example.sentence: It's <highlight>fine</highlight> today.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今天天气很好。

word_usage.usage: 表示“美好的, 优秀的”时，fine有比较级finer和最高级finest。
表“健康的, 身体很好的”时，fine没有比较级和最高级。

fine表“天气晴朗的”时，主语多用it。
示例：It was another fine winter day. 
又是一个晴朗的冬日。
fine表“罚金”时，为可数名词，注意单复数。

fine作动词，表“处...以罚金”时，多以被动形式出现。
示例：She was fined for speeding.
她因超速而被罚款。
